You can safely remove `args: Array&lt;String&gt;` if you won&#39;t use it. The compiler just warns you that you have unused things. You can even remove the outer `Main` class. It&#39;s not necessary in Kotlin.
```
fun main() {
    println(&quot;sss&quot;)
}
```

The problem is that you declared `main` function as an instance method of the class `Main`.

In Kotlin an entry-point `main` function can be declared either on top-level (i.e. not in any class, just in a package)

```
package samplePackage // optional package name

fun main(args: Array&lt;String&gt;) {
}
```

or in an object or companion object:

```
object Main {
    @JvmStatic
    fun main(args: Array&lt;String&gt;) {
    }
}
```

